            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EGodly%20sorrow%20for%20sin%20is%20often%20confused%20with%20regret.%20Tears%20and%20remorse%20are%20no%20true%20indication%20that%20a%20person%20has%20truly%20repented%20of%20sin.%20He%20may%20be%20crying%20simply%20because%20he%20got%20caught%2C%20not%20because%20he%20is%20genuinely%20repentant!%20The%20real%20test%20of%20repentance%20is%20evidenced%20by%20submission%2C%20actions%20that%20show%20one%20has%20submitted%20to%20the%20authority%20of%20another.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAfter%20challenging%20the%20Corinthian%20believers%20to%20discipline%20a%20brother%20who%20had%20fallen%20into%20immorality%2C%20Paul%20commended%20them%20on%20their%20response%20to%20his%20instructions.%20He%20said%2C%20%22Just%20see%20what%20this%20godly%20sorrow%20produced%20in%20you!%20Such%20earnestness%2C%20such%20concern%20to%20clear%20yourselves%2C%20such%20indignation%2C%20such%20alarm%2C%20such%20longing%20to%20see%20me%2C%20such%20zeal%2C%20and%20such%20a%20readiness%20to%20punish%20the%20wrongdoer.%20You%20showed%20that%20you%20have%20done%20everything%20you%20could%20to%20make%20things%20right%22%20(2%20Corinthians%207%3A11).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWorldly%20sorrow%20is%20simply%20regret.%20It%20produces%20blaming%20others%2C%20emotional%20shows%2C%20dodging%20of%20facts%2C%20half-confessions%20(%22If%20I've%20done%20anything%20wrong%20.%20.%20.%22)%2C%20and%20insincere%20promises%20to%20change.%20Godly%20sorrow%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20assumes%20responsibility%2C%20faces%20the%20facts%2C%20admits%20the%20wrong%2C%20and%20makes%20it%20right.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20Corinthians%20demonstrated%20true%20godly%20sorrow.%20They%20were%20alarmed%20over%20their%20sin%2C%20desirous%20to%20right%20the%20wrong%2C%20eager%20to%20address%20the%20issue%2C%20and%20ready%20to%20make%20things%20right.%20In%20a%20word%2C%20they%20submitted%20themselves%20to%20Paul's%20authority%20and%20were%20willing%20to%20take%20the%20necessary%20steps%20to%20right%20their%20wrong.%20Such%20action%2C%20not%20emotional%20regret%2C%20indicates%20godly%20sorrow.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
